reut2-003.sgm, JAPANESE CRUSHERS BUY CANADIAN RAPESEED, Japanese crushers bought 5,000 to 7,000tonnes of Canadian rapeseed in export business over the weekendfor April shipment, trade sources said.    Japanese crushers continue to concentrate on rapeseedpurchases since it converts to a higher percentage of oil thanother oilseeds, they said. A glut of feed meals makes otheroilseeds, such as soybeans, less desirable because they wouldadd to already large meal stocks. Reuter&#3;
