reut2-003.sgm, EMERY AIR &lt;EAF> FEBRUARY SHIPMENTS UP 12 PCT, Emergy Air Freight Corp said itsshipments rose 12 pct to 1,190,000 last month from 1,067,000 inFebruary 1986.    The company said the weight of these shipments was up 20pct to 52.7 mln pounds from 44.0 mln a year earlier. Reuter&#3;
reut2-003.sgm, UNION, SHIPPERS AGREE TO CUT N.Y. PORT COSTS, The New York Shipping Association andInternational Longshoremen's Association said they agreed tocut cargo assessments at the Port of New York and New Jersey bymore than 50 pct on some labor intensive cargos.    The charges on cargo handled by union workers will bereduced to 2.85 dlrs a ton from 5.85 dlrs a ton, effectiveApril one, according to the agreement between the union andshippers. The assessments are used to fund workers' benefits.    What were doing is lowering the price to get more bulkcargo flowing through here

