reut2-003.sgm, TURKISH WEATHER IMPROVES, BUT BRINGS FLOODS, Turkish banks and government officesreopened here after snow blanketing the city began to melt,causing floods and traffic jams.    Turkish radio said 16 villages in the southern province ofHatay were evacuated after the Karasu river burst its banks,flooding 5,000 hectares of crops.    The radio said cold weather and snow still covered much ofcentral and eastern Anatolia, the Asian part of the country,and two people were frozen to death near the town of Corum. Theweather office in Istanbul said the cold front was moving eastand conditions should be back to normal by the weekend. Reuter&#3;
